HEADWORD: Flesher
<hw>Flesh"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
butcher.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>flesher</qex> on a block had laid his whittle down.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A two-handled, convex, blunt-edged knife, for
scraping hides; a fleshing knife.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fleshhood</ent>⟦br⟧
